# Theme PHP Conventions

- Classic PHP templates — no block theme, no FSE, no page builders
- Use `get_template_part()` for all reusable sections
- Wrap user-facing strings in `__()` or `_e()` with `'jjbbq'` text domain
- Template parts live in `template-parts/` directory
- Helper functions live in `inc/template-functions.php`
- Images must have `loading="lazy"` and proper `alt` attributes
- Include `wp_head()` before `</head>` and `wp_footer()` before `</body>`
- Use `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()` for output escaping
